reviewText: T​he course was fine, but it is very confusing as to how to complete a section and how to get your certificate. On the page, it says that everything is complete, but on the Coursera page, it says that I am only 98% complete. If I only want to do the one course, how do I get the certificate of completion for it?  Very confusing compared to other courses I've taken on Coursera.
I love everything about the course what I didn't enjoy that much is the peer assignments and gradings.

The course was adequate, and sometimes good, but many times I wished more exampes were used; when a video example or images of a feature was presented, it was such a breath of fresh air to see just what the presenter was talking about. More details about these, and seeing them more in use, would help. A few other comments might be that the transcripts really could use paragraphs (and to be checked, as sometimes they were not accurate), and a 20:00 video is a little too long when it is just presenting loads of data. The presenters are OK, but some are a bit stilted and the main presenter, while very personable, sometimes slurs his words or ideas.
I​t was good to learn certain usefull concepts. please also include some practicle learning in it.
